<TITLE> South Africa to play underprivileged kids in exhibition match </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 9 (bdnews24.com)  The visiting South African cricket squad are to play an exhibition match against a team comprised of underprivileged youths from Sir Salimullaj Orphanage and Warid Telecom staff, said a press release Sunday. The Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium will see the touring Proteas side pit their wits against the local squad on Monday at one in the afternoon. The match will consist of 10-over-a-side. The event has been organised on the sidelines of the 'Warid Cricket Series', and is intended to inspire some happy moments for the underprivileged kids at the orphanage, said the press release. Warid Telecom will also present some cricket equipment to Sir Salimullah Orphanage. The Proteas team will have to score double the runs of their opponents to ensure a victory, while the locals need only register half of the South African team's total to seal their triumph. bd
